Thank you for submitting a pull request! 

All kinds of pull request are welcome: improving styles, fixing bugs, better cross-platform performance, improved UI, and so on. 
However, for any large changes to the text of the book or the examples, please get in touch with me on lewy@discoverthreejs.com - or start a discussion [here](https://github.com/looeee/discoverthreejs-site/discussions) describing your propose changes - before opening a pull request. 
For small changes such as minor rewording, grammar fixes, errata or other changes, go right ahead :) 

* **What kind of change does this PR introduce?** (Bug fix, feature, text update, ...)


* **What is the current behavior?** (You can also link to an open issue here)



* **What is the new behavior (if this is a feature change)?**



* **Does this PR introduce a breaking change?** 



* **Other information**:
